WEBVTT

00:04.238 --> 00:05.272 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF, PBS NEWSHOUR
ANCHOR: Good evening.

00:05.305 --> 00:06.540 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I'’m Judy Woodruff.

00:06.573 --> 00:08.709 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN, PBS NEWSHOUR:
And I'’m
Hari Sreenivasan.

00:08.742 --> 00:12.679 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WOODRUFF: On the "NewsHour"
tonight: as President-elect
Trump continues to build the
future administration,

00:12.713 --> 00:18.051 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a look at the most pressing
questions around
the role his children will play
and potential

00:18.085 --> 00:19.953 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
conflicts of interest.

00:19.987 --> 00:24.791 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SREENIVASAN: Also ahead this
Thursday, evacuations
begin in war-ravaged Aleppo as a
cease-fire

00:24.825 --> 00:28.829 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
allows Syrians to escape from
the battle's
bloody end.

00:28.862 --> 00:32.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOODRUFF: And, economists put
their money
where their mouth is.

00:32.599 --> 00:37.371 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
After grave mistakes in
prediction polls,
the betting markets feel the
loss.

00:37.404 --> 00:39.172 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(BEGIN VIDEO CLIP)

00:39.206 --> 00:41.174 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
UNIDENTIFIED MALE: One of the
things that
we learn here, and this is a
lesson for both

00:41.208 --> 00:45.178 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
the media and for social
scientists, is how
difficult it is to communicate
clearly about

00:45.212 --> 00:46.179 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
probabilities.

00:46.213 --> 00:47.447 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(END VIDEO CLIP)

00:47.481 --> 00:54.321 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SREENIVASAN: All that and more
on tonight's
PBS "NewsHour".

00:54.354 --> 00:57.791 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

00:57.824 --> 01:07.234 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WOODRUFF: Convoys of buses
carried some 3,000
people out of eastern Aleppo in
Syria today,

01:07.267 --> 01:09.202 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
under a cease-fire arrangement.

01:09.236 --> 01:14.942 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Their evacuation to Idlib
province effectively
marked the end of rebel
resistance in that

01:14.975 --> 01:16.710 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
city.

01:16.743 --> 01:20.948 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In Washington, Secretary of
State John Kerry
called again for peace talks, as
he blasted

01:20.981 --> 01:22.049 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the Syrian government.

01:22.082 --> 01:23.850 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(BEGIN VIDEO CLIP)

01:23.884 --> 01:26.286 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN KERRY, SECRETARY OF STATE:
The Assad
regime is actually carrying out
nothing short

01:26.320 --> 01:28.221 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of a massacre.

01:28.255 --> 01:37.798 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And we have witnessed
indiscriminate slaughter,
not accidents of war, not
collateral damage,

01:37.831 --> 01:39.132 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
but frankly purposeful.

01:39.166 --> 01:40.968 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(END VIDEO CLIP)

01:41.001 --> 01:44.438 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WOODRUFF: The White House said
President Obama
spoke with Turkey's President
Tayyip Recap

01:44.471 --> 01:48.342 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Erdogan by phone and thanked him
for brokering
the truce.

01:48.375 --> 01:53.814 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And Syria's President Bashar
al-Assad likened
the fall of Aleppo to the birth
of Christ

01:53.847 --> 01:56.450 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
or the revelation of the Koran.

01:56.483 --> 01:59.052 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We'll get a report from Aleppo
later in the
program.

01:59.086 --> 02:03.523 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SREENIVASAN: In the day's other
news, President-elect
Trump checked another box on his
cabinet list.

02:03.557 --> 02:06.626 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He chose Congressman Ryan Zinke
for interior
secretary.

02:06.660 --> 02:11.598 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Montana Republican is a
former Navy SEAL
who is finishing his first term
in the U.S.

02:11.631 --> 02:13.333 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
House.

02:13.367 --> 02:16.603 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Zinke has pushed for energy
independence and
voted to expand oil and gas
drilling.

02:16.636 --> 02:21.808 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WOODRUFF: A jury in Charleston,
South Carolina,
has convicted Dylann Roof, in
the killing

02:21.842 --> 02:24.678 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of nine black church-goers last
year.

02:24.711 --> 02:29.716 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The white supremacist was found
guilty today
of federal hate crimes and other
counts.

02:29.750 --> 02:36.089 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In closing arguments, the
prosecution called
Roof a cold, calculated killer,
full of hate.

02:36.123 --> 02:40.761 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The defense admitted his guilt,
but focused
on trying to prevent a death
sentence.

02:40.794 --> 02:45.198 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SREENIVASAN: Bitterly cold air
swept down
from Canada and engulfed the
Upper Midwest

02:45.232 --> 02:47.100 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
today, spreading to the East
Coast.

02:47.134 --> 02:51.838 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Temperatures were frigid and
fell below zero
in parts of North Dakota,
Minnesota and Wisconsin,

02:51.872 --> 02:56.243 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
where wind chills made it even
colder -- 15
to 30 degrees below zero.

02:56.276 --> 03:00.313 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Arctic blast also brought
snow from the
Great Lakes to the Northeast,
and caused a

03:00.347 --> 03:03.050 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
pileup of about 60 cars in
Western Pennsylvania.

03:03.083 --> 03:04.084 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(BEGIN VIDEO CLIP)

03:04.117 --> 03:06.186 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUSTIN ROSS, DRIVER: Traffic was
stopped.

03:06.219 --> 03:08.021 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I tried to stop.

03:08.055 --> 03:12.826 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I got pushed over into another
lane, and I
stopped and other cars started
coming along,

03:12.859 --> 03:14.594 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
truck passed over.

03:14.628 --> 03:19.666 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He was going about 60, got into
the ditch
and it just started piling up
after that.

03:19.699 --> 03:21.635 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(END VIDEO CLIP)

03:21.668 --> 03:26.006 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SREENIVASAN: Overnight, light
snow from another
storm system caused commuter
havoc in Portland,

03:26.039 --> 03:29.643 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Oregon, with multiple crashes
and traffic
backed up for miles.

03:29.676 --> 03:35.248 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WOODRUFF: The 320,000 residents
of Corpus
Christi, Texas, are being urged
not to drink

03:35.282 --> 03:38.051 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
their tap water until further
notice.

03:38.085 --> 03:43.523 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
City officials say it might be
contaminated
with chemicals from an
industrial leak yesterday.

03:43.557 --> 03:48.361 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The warning has caused a run on
bottled water,
with long lines at grocery
stores across the

03:48.395 --> 03:50.163 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
city.

03:50.197 --> 03:53.900 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Schools are also closed, and
it's not clear
when the drinking supply will be
safe again.

03:53.934 --> 03:58.772 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SREENIVASAN: An ex-police
officer in Milwaukee
has been charged with reckless
homicide in

03:58.805 --> 04:00.640 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
a fatal shooting that sparked
riots.

04:00.674 --> 04:05.112 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
A criminal complaint released
today says the
victim was armed, but threw away
his gun moments

04:05.145 --> 04:06.513 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
before he was killed.

04:06.546 --> 04:09.749 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The officer was fired later,
over a separate
incident.

04:09.783 --> 04:14.154 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And in Pasco, Washington, a
coroner's jury
cleared three state police
officers.

04:14.187 --> 04:18.158 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They shot and killed an unarmed
Mexican farm
worker after he threw rocks at
them.

04:18.191 --> 04:23.897 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WOODRUFF: The United States
today renewed
sanctions against Iran for
another 10 years.

04:23.930 --> 04:29.769 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The extension became law
automatically when
President Obama declined to sign
or veto the

04:29.803 --> 04:31.605 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
bill.

04:31.638 --> 04:35.275 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The White House says the
president will waive
most of the sanctions, but it's
warning Congress

04:35.308 --> 04:39.045 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
against doing anything else to
undo the nuclear
deal with Iran.

04:39.079 --> 04:40.814 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(BEGIN VIDEO CLIP)

04:40.847 --> 04:42.215 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOSH EARNEST, WHITE HOUSE PRESS
SECRETARY:
The president did not veto this
bill because

04:42.249 --> 04:44.050 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
it does not undermine the deal.

04:44.084 --> 04:48.855 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But there'’s been plenty of
rhetoric and
plenty of legislative work done
on legislation

04:48.889 --> 04:50.790 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
that would blow up the deal.

04:50.824 --> 04:55.061 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And this is a message that if
the United States
Congress blows up the deal that
prevents Iran

04:55.095 --> 04:59.933 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
from obtaining a nuclear weapon,
they will
have to deal with the grave
consequences that

04:59.966 --> 05:01.001 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
ensue.

05:01.034 --> 05:02.769 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(END VIDEO CLIP)

05:02.802 --> 05:06.640 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
WOODRUFF: Iran says the
sanctions renewal
does violate the nuclear deal,
and it vows

05:06.673 --> 05:08.575 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to respond.

05:08.608 --> 05:12.546 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SREENIVASAN: Investigators in
Egypt say they've
found traces of explosives on
victims of an

05:12.579 --> 05:14.314 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Egypt Air crash in May.

05:14.347 --> 05:18.685 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
All 66 people on board died when
the flight
plunged into the Mediterranean
Sea.

05:18.718 --> 05:22.289 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Search crews were able to
recover a variety
of wreckage from the sea floor.

05:22.322 --> 05:25.692 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The plane had been on a flight
from Paris
to Cairo.

05:25.725 --> 05:28.695 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There has been no claim of
responsibility
for downing the airliner.

05:28.728 --> 05:33.233 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WOODRUFF: Back in this country,
U.S. Labor
Secretary Thomas Perez announced
he's running

05:33.266 --> 05:36.069 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
for chair of the Democratic
National Committee.

05:36.102 --> 05:39.005 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He'll take on Congressman Keith
Ellison of
Minnesota.

05:39.039 --> 05:45.078 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The state party heads in South
Carolina and
New Hampshire, Jaime Harrison
and Ray Buckley,

05:45.111 --> 05:46.947 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
are also running.

05:46.980 --> 05:51.151 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SREENIVASAN: As of today,
recreational use
of marijuana is officially legal
in Massachusetts.

05:51.184 --> 05:55.522 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's the first state on the
Eastern Seaboard
to take that step, and one of
eight states

05:55.555 --> 05:57.324 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
nationwide.

05:57.357 --> 06:00.126 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The ballot measure, passed last
month, allows
adults to grow and use limited
amounts of

06:00.160 --> 06:02.062 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
marijuana at their homes.

06:02.095 --> 06:06.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It will be another year before
retail pot
shops are allowed to open.

06:06.199 --> 06:09.869 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOODRUFF: And, Wall Street
rebounded some
from yesterday's losses.

06:09.903 --> 06:17.244 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The Dow Jones industrial average
gained 59
points to close at 19,852, the
NASDAQ rose

06:17.277 --> 06:19.980 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
20 points, and the S&amp;P 500 added
eight.

06:20.013 --> 06:24.251 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SREENIVASAN: Still to come on
the "NewsHour":
the Trump family's role in the
administration

06:24.284 --> 06:30.156 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and business; the last survivors
evacuate
in the Syrian city of Aleppo;
evidence of

06:30.190 --> 06:38.064 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Vladimir Putin's involvement in
the hack leading
up to the election, and much
more.

06:38.098 --> 06:41.868 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
(BREAK)

06:41.901 --> 06:49.743 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WOODRUFF: Today was supposed to
be the day
President-elect Trump held a
news conference,

06:49.776 --> 06:55.181 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to spell out what role, if any,
he would play
in the future of his business
empire.

06:55.215 --> 06:59.052 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He's since postponed talking to
the press
about it, at least until
January.

06:59.085 --> 07:04.958 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Instead, today, he tweeted with
a push back
against all of speculation about
potential

07:04.991 --> 07:06.726 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
conflicts of interest.

07:06.760 --> 07:11.231 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He wrote, quote, "The media
tries so hard
to make my move to the White
House, as it

07:11.264 --> 07:16.102 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
pertains to my business, so
complex -- when
actually it isn't!"

07:16.136 --> 07:19.939 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But there's also this from one
of his top
aides, Kellyanne Conway.

07:19.973 --> 07:24.010 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She told MSNBC this morning that
there was
still work to be done.

07:24.044 --> 07:25.912 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(BEGIN VIDEO CLIP)

07:25.945 --> 07:26.946 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
KELLYANNE CONWAY, SENIOR
ADVISER, TRUMP TRANSITION
TEAM: Getting this right, before
you announce

07:26.980 --> 07:28.782 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
it, is what's important.

07:28.815 --> 07:31.151 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That's what I'’ve been told by
the legal
experts and the other protocol
experts -- to

07:31.184 --> 07:35.588 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
make sure that the structure
that's put in
place shows the complete
separation, so that

07:35.622 --> 07:40.160 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Donald Trump himself as the
president of the
United States, Steve, can focus
100 percent

07:40.193 --> 07:41.661 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
on being president of the United
States.

07:41.695 --> 07:42.996 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's going to take a little bit
longer.

07:43.029 --> 07:44.698 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(END VIDEO CLIP)

07:44.731 --> 07:48.468 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WOODRUFF: Meanwhile, there's new
pressure
today from a group of Senate
Democrats, who

07:48.501 --> 07:53.807 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
unveiled a bill that would
require Mr. Trump
to divest from his businesses,
and put his

07:53.840 --> 07:55.975 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
assets in a blind trust.

07:56.009 --> 08:01.147 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Here now to unpack those
possible conflicts
of interests are Marilyn Geewax.

08:01.181 --> 08:04.417 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
She'’s senior business editor for
NPR.

08:04.451 --> 08:09.122 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And Richard Painter, he's a
professor at the
University of Minnesota Law
School and he

08:09.155 --> 08:13.526 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
was a White House ethics adviser
for President
George W. Bush.

08:13.560 --> 08:16.029 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And we welcome both of you to
the program.

08:16.062 --> 08:19.532 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Marilyn Geewax, let me start
with you, what
do we know about why this
announcement is

08:19.566 --> 08:21.434 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
being postponed?

08:21.468 --> 08:24.971 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARILYN GEEWAX, NPRR: We know
very little,
other than what he tweets but
one can speculate.

08:25.004 --> 08:30.810 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He had said several weeks ago
that he would
have this press conference
today, on the 15th,

08:30.844 --> 08:32.879 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and on Monday, he said, never
mind.

08:32.912 --> 08:34.681 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I'’m not really going to do that.

08:34.714 --> 08:39.219 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, people are speculating that
some think
he wanted to wait until after
the Electoral

08:39.252 --> 08:41.054 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
College votes.

08:41.087 --> 08:44.758 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Others say the business is just
so complicated
that it's going to take more
legal work to

08:44.791 --> 08:48.928 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
figure out how to pull him out
of it.

08:48.962 --> 08:54.667 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And others just say that this is
just kind
of a general smokescreen, that
you could say

08:54.701 --> 08:58.738 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
you're going to do this, you
stall for two
weeks, then he says he's going
to do it, but

08:58.772 --> 09:00.507 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
now, he's going to stall longer.

09:00.540 --> 09:04.411 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And by the time he does get to
this topic,
it will be January, and we'll be
focused on

09:04.444 --> 09:06.713 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the inauguration and it will
seem smaller.

09:06.746 --> 09:10.850 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WOODRUFF: Well, Richard Painter,
as we just
reported, Mr. Trump tweeted
today.

09:10.884 --> 09:13.286 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
You know, it's not complex.

09:13.319 --> 09:16.990 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
On the other hand, we just heard
Kellyanne
Conway, we've heard some of his
other advisers

09:17.023 --> 09:19.926 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
say, well, there is more work to
