38:14.592 --> 38:15.727 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
a fix.

38:15.760 --> 38:17.262 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Your folks at "Slate" had
actually worked
on a tool.

38:17.295 --> 38:21.065 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You guys just launched this, not
coincidentally
on Monday.

38:21.099 --> 38:22.767 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Let's take a look at how this
works.

38:22.800 --> 38:25.069 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We'’re going to put this up on
the screen
here.

38:25.103 --> 38:29.908 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, if I come across a fake news
story in
my feed, and there's this big
red banner saying,

38:29.941 --> 38:31.109 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
"This news story is fake.

38:31.142 --> 38:32.110 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Here's how we know.

38:32.143 --> 38:33.111 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Share the proof."

38:33.144 --> 38:34.112 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
How do you know?

38:34.145 --> 38:35.113 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Identify by this as fake.

38:35.146 --> 38:36.114 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
This is the tool.

38:36.147 --> 38:37.916 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
OREMUS: Yes, that'’s right.

38:37.949 --> 38:40.218 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, what we wanted to do was not
just flag
stories as fake when they appear
in your Facebook

38:40.251 --> 38:42.020 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
feed.

38:42.053 --> 38:44.355 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We actually wanted to give users
the power
to do something about it,
because -- I mean,

38:44.389 --> 38:46.591 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
it's so frustrating, right?

38:46.624 --> 38:51.396 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You try to be a good consumer of
the media,
you try to evaluate what's true
and what's

38:51.429 --> 38:54.232 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
credible, but then you see
friends and relatives
sharing this stuff.

38:54.265 --> 38:59.504 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, what we do is we actually
provide a link
to a reputable debunking of that
particular

38:59.537 --> 39:01.739 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
story that will appear
automatically.

39:01.773 --> 39:05.643 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And then we prompt you to share
that link
with the person who posted the
fake news so

39:05.677 --> 39:09.847 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that they and all of their
followers can see
that that story is fake or they
can go to

39:09.881 --> 39:11.649 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the debunking site and judge of
the evidence
for themselves.

39:11.683 --> 39:15.520 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SREENIVASAN: Now, there's a tool
you can actually
add to your browser.

39:15.553 --> 39:19.424 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's kind of an extension, a
Chrome extension
and a button that works there.

39:19.457 --> 39:21.960 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We can look at other examples of
stories as
well.

39:21.993 --> 39:23.928 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
