JACQUELINE NOVOGRATZ, FOUNDER
AND CEO OF ACUMEN:
When I was six years old, my
first grade nun,

50:07.705 --> 50:12.643 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Sister Mary Theophane, beat it
into my head
to whom much is given much is
expected.

50:12.676 --> 50:14.545 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And so, I always wanted to
change the world.

50:14.578 --> 50:20.618 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I moved to Rwanda to help start
the first
micro finance bank and soon
thereafter realized

50:20.651 --> 50:23.554 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that most people don't want
saving.

50:23.587 --> 50:29.793 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Most people want choice and
opportunity, which
is another way of saying
dignity.

50:29.827 --> 50:40.271 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In a funny way, I became an
accidental banker
and ended up in Latin America
during the financial

50:40.304 --> 50:42.172 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
debt crisis of the early 1980s.

50:42.206 --> 50:45.042 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And there I saw that I love the
tools of business.

50:45.075 --> 50:50.848 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The problem was that low-income
people who
were so industrious had no
access to the banks

50:50.881 --> 50:55.185 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and that's why I went into
international development
and saw that on the other side,
there was

50:55.219 --> 51:00.991 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a great humanitarian ethos, but
it lacked
the efficiency, the
effectiveness of the markets.

51:01.025 --> 51:05.095 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We often say the market is the
best listening
device that we have.

51:05.129 --> 51:11.769 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, if I give you a gift, you're
unlikely
to tell me what you don't like
about it.

51:11.802 --> 51:18.976 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But if I try to tell you a solar
light, you're
going to tell me exactly what
you think.

51:19.009 --> 51:22.646 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We created an organization with
this idea
that you could change the way
the world tackles

51:22.680 --> 51:27.151 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
poverty by using something we
call "patient
capital."

51:27.184 --> 51:33.157 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We took philanthropy and rather
than give
it away, we would invest it in
intrepid entrepreneurs

51:33.190 --> 51:39.029 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that were going where both
markets and government
aid had failed the poor, basic
services like

51:39.063 --> 51:44.335 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
