agriculture, energy,
workforce development.

51:44.368 --> 51:49.773 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What entrepreneurs and others
we've invested
in have in common is what we
call moral imagination.

51:49.807 --> 51:54.111 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Moral imagination starts with
putting yourself
in another person's shoes and
seeing the world

51:54.144 --> 51:55.913 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
through their perspective.

51:55.946 --> 51:57.715 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
But it's more than empathy.

51:57.748 --> 52:03.821 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's the ability to envision a
world and build
institutions in which all people
matter.

52:03.854 --> 52:09.660 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, often, we look at poverty in
terms of
how much a person makes, rather
than understand

52:09.693 --> 52:13.230 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
their contribution as a human
being.

52:13.263 --> 52:19.703 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
When we see companies enable
people to have
access to clean drinking water
or agricultural

52:19.737 --> 52:25.409 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
inputs that enable them to make
a little more
income, one of the first things
they do is

52:25.442 --> 52:28.212 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
turn around and help somebody
else.

52:28.245 --> 52:32.916 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's seeing that there is no one
above you
or below you.

52:32.950 --> 52:39.256 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And really that's the world that
we need on
see right now when we are so
divided, and

52:39.289 --> 52:43.127 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
yet have so much opportunity to
become united.

52:43.160 --> 52:44.895 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
My name is Jacqueline Novogratz.

